{
  "title": "Refactoring REST APIs using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This explainer provides an overview of how to use FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI leverages type hints and Pydantic models for improved developer productivity",
    "It supports OpenAPI 3.0 specifications and automatic documentation generation",
    "FastAPI includes a powerful router system for modularization",
    "Depends on ASGI (Async Server Gateway Interface) for asynchronous web applications"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n@app.get('/items/{item_id}')\ndef read_item(item_id: int):\n    return {'item': {'id': item_id, 'name': f'Item {item_id}'}}``"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\nfrom fastapi.responses import JSONResponse\nclass Item(BaseModel):\n    name: str\n@app.get('/items/{item_id}')\ndef read_item(item_id: int, item: Item = Depends(get_item)):\n    return JSONResponse({'item': item})``"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for using FastAPI and its dependencies",
    "FastAPI version 0.78.0 or higher is recommended"
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "When using Pydantic models, ensure that all required fields are defined with appropriate data types",
    "Correctly configure the ASGI server for deployment (e.g., Uvicorn or Hypercorn)"
  ]
